# Trivy CVE allowlist — OPS-3 / build-and-push security gate.
#
# Each entry MUST include the CVE ID, the package, the rationale, and an
# expiry date. CI re-evaluates on every build; an unjustified entry will be
# spotted in code review.
#
# REQUIRED machine-readable fields (parsed by api/scripts/check-trivyignore.mjs):
#   Reviewed:    <YYYY-MM-DD>   when the rationale below was last validated
#   Re-check-by: <YYYY-MM-DD>   deadline for the next periodic review
#                               (script default cadence: 90 days)
#
# Trivy itself only reads bare CVE IDs; the surrounding comments are for
# humans and the review-staleness check (.github/workflows/trivyignore-review.yml).

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CVE-2026-4800 — lodash 4.17.21 → "fixed" in 4.18.0
# Package: lodash (transitive via @chevrotain/cst-dts-gen, @chevrotain/gast,
#                  pulled in by Prisma 7's @prisma/internals)
# Rationale: lodash 4.18.0 was published, then deprecated by the maintainers
#            with the explicit notice "Bad release. Please use lodash@4.17.21
#            instead." (visible via `npm view lodash@4.18.0`). Forcing 4.18.0
#            via npm overrides reintroduces a regression worse than the CVE
#            (which requires attacker-controlled input to a lodash sink we do
#            not expose — chevrotain only uses lodash internally for AST work
#            on Prisma schema files at build time, never at request time).
# Owner:       @pranems
# Reviewed:    2026-04-30
# Re-check-by: 2026-07-30
# Re-check action: when chevrotain or lodash publishes a real fix, drop the
#                  override and remove this entry.
CVE-2026-4800

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CVE-2026-33671 - picomatch 4.0.3 ReDoS (extglob patterns)
# Package: picomatch (bundled inside the base image's npm CLI at
#          /usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/node_modules/tinyglobby/node_modules/picomatch)
# Rationale: This is npm's INTERNAL copy of picomatch shipped inside the
#            node:24-alpine base image. It is unreachable by package.json
#            overrides because npm is a global tool, not a project dep. npm
#            only processes file-system glob patterns supplied by package.json
#            authors and CLI flags - never attacker-controlled HTTP input.
#            The runtime risk is zero. The proper fix is a base-image bump
#            once node:24-alpine ships an npm with the patched tinyglobby.
# Owner:       @pranems
# Reviewed:    2026-04-30
# Re-check-by: 2026-07-30
# Re-check action: monitor https://github.com/nodejs/docker-node/releases for
#                  an updated node:24-alpine; remove this entry when
#                  `docker run --rm node:24-alpine npm exec -- node -p
#                   "require('picomatch/package.json').version"` reports >= 4.0.4.
CVE-2026-33671
